body.content: Warning: The following contains reference to violence. Bartomoleo — Henny Scott was 14 years old when she went missing on the Northern Cheyenne Indian reservation. Twenty days later, a search party found her body covered in snow 200 yards from where she was last seen. Officials said she died from hypothermia, despite bruises and a broken nose, leaving her community with unanswered questions. Petition starter Jillian says Henny and her family deserve justice. Sign now to urge the FBI and Bureau of Indian affairs to reopen her case. REOPEN HENNY’S CASE 14,283 have signed Jillian Norton’s petition. Let’s get to 15,000! 14 year old Henny Scott was last seen December 8th 2018 when she allegedly walked away from a residence in the Muddy Creek area west of Lame Deer on the Northern Cheyenne Indian Reservation. When the mother of Henny, Paula Castro Stops, reported her daughter missing there was no amber alert or immediate official search. Henny’s body was found on Dec 28th covered in snow only 200 yards behind the residence in Muddy Creek. It was ruled that she passed away from hypothermia. However I’m making this petition to ask the FBI and Bureau of Indian Affairs to consider reopening Henny’s case. With your help we could possibly bring justice and answers to Henny’s loved ones.  Sign now with a click https://click.e.change.org/f/a/Bkd-kYJi3vlL1oxD_eiTxw~~/AANj1QA~~ Visit petition page https://click.e.change.org/f/a/_onkh-AUb0_4oAvnIDY6IA~~/AANj1QA~~ At Change.org, we believe in the voice of everyday people.
